          "id": "1744cc23d0ad_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "fb61",
          "text": "The map below, produced by Carbon Tracker, shows that while the potential fossil fuel reserves left, might be twice as much as the current listed reserves, the carbon budget we have to stick to in order to have 50% chance to stay under 1.5 ºC of global average warming is less than a fifth of current fossil fuel reserves. Peak oil will not be the driver to get humanity off its fossil fuel addiction; climate change will have to be that driver, if we hope to secure a thriving future for humanity and the rest of the community of life.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
