        {
          "id": "1744cc23d0ad_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e505",
          "text": "That said, the conversation about peak oil has been useful and will continue to influence decision makers. One excellent resource on the topic is the website ‘The Oil Drum. The production of sweet crude oil did peak in 2005 and has declined ever since. The fossil fuel industries has responded with exploiting and listing very more hard-to-get-at reserves (both financially and technically) and has thereby shows that we are long way of peak-fossil-fuel (see graph below) if the only driver are available reserves. Nevertheless, it has become clear that we will have to wean humanity of its fossil fuel addiction and create a global shift not only towards renewable energy but also towards a material culture that is far less dependent on fossil (non-renewable) resources.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
